<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Global Product Solutions - Corporate Debt Products</H1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Corporate Debt Products group is responsible for underwriting, originating, and managing the credit and market risks associated with Global Corporate and Investment Banking loan and trading portfolios. The team uses cutting–edge risk management techniques to support our commitment to reduce credit and trading loss volatility.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
As an Associate in Asia, you will assist the Corporate Debt Products team by: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Performing qualitative and quantitative due diligence on industry and company dynamics </li>
    <li>Helping to control the bank’s credit exposure</li> 
    <li>Creating bank debt solutions to meet client capital needs</li> 
    <li>Researching, organizing and presenting critical information impacting immediate credit decisions</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain an MBA degree a premier business school.  Candidate should have deep and broad finance knowledge, financial and accounting proficiency, excellent verbal and written communication skills, strategic and creative thinking, quantitative skills, and strong personal leadership skills.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">
Associates will participate in an orientation program and formal learning curriculum to learn more about the bank’s business, culture and values.  Throughout the program, you’ll have ample opportunities to work closely with professionals and peers throughout our organization. This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company that will prove to be a tremendous resource to you throughout your career.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Placement</h2>
<p class="bac">
Associates work in Mumbai or New Delhi, India. Offers are made for a specific product desk, based on candidate preference and business need.  Throughout the recruiting and orientation process, candidates have the opportunities to learn about various desks and meet team members and colleagues from across the company.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">How to Apply</h2>
<p class="bac">
Please follow any procedures set forth through the Career Services office on your campus.
</p>

